From 05b42d7dfc1faa5d24e60b302d535ef76956ee6b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Bill Hlavacek <hlavacek@lanl.gov>
Date: Sun, 22 Feb 2026 01:59:39 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 05/14] bngsim: convert exit(1) calls to throw
 std::runtime_error
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Originally landed as PyBNF-Private bngsim commit 9c77d2ec ("Session 29:
NFsim tech debt elimination", Feb 22 2026), but that work was written
directly into bngsim/third_party/nfsim/ instead of being staged here on
bngsim/vendor. The May-15 PyBNF-Private refresh (008529a7) faithfully
replayed the recorded 13-patch carry queue and silently reverted those
58 conversions, breaking BNGL models with local-function rate laws
(crash in CompositeFunction::evaluateOn). This carry restores the work
on the proper branch so future vendor_nfsim.py refreshes preserve it.

Files: moleculeType.cpp (10 conversions), system.cpp (14),
compositeFunction.cpp (5), function.cpp (5), NFinput.cpp (11),
reaction.cpp (7). Of Session 29's original 58 conversions, 52 apply
directly; the other 6 sites in compositeFunction.cpp::loadParamFile,
function.cpp::loadParamFile, and the related enableFileDependency
catches were superseded by upstream NFsim refactoring (use of
NFutil::loadTimeSeries and pre-existing throws by Achyudhan Kutuva
in April 2026) — those code paths no longer have exit(1) callsites.

Each conversion adds #include <stdexcept> if not already present and
extracts the failure context from the adjacent cerr/cout messages so
the thrown what() reports something diagnosable. Malformed XML and
all six file-class error paths now propagate as std::runtime_error
that can be caught and translated to RuntimeError by the bngsim host.
---
